Meet <b>Amber</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Amber lives at <a href='/home/?user=ihopeyoudance32'>72843 Bluebird Street</a> in one of the tall, historic houses of Lakeview.  She's been inspired by the neighborhood's lakeside views since she moved in on February 25, 2006.<br><br>The most striking aspect of Amber's personality is her creativity.  She loves to find new and exciting ways in which to express herself.  Amber has always enjoyed singing and often challenges herself by performing songs from many different musical styles.  Every time she sings a song, Amber tries to put as much of herself into it as she can.  <br><br>Amber also brings this type of expressiveness to her other hobby &mdash; drawing.  Her pictures are bright, vibrant, and filled with brilliant shades of green, light blue, and gold, which happen to be her favorite colors.  Whether her drawings are realistic or more abstract, Amber always tries to show the viewer something different and unique.<br><br>In her spare time, Amber likes hanging out at the mall with her friends and doing some shopping.  She loves to read, which is why Amber often spends hours at <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=2">Bookends Book Shop</a>, browsing the shelves in search of a good book.  When she's not deeply immersed in her latest novel, Amber can usually be found at a football game, cheering on her favorite team from the stands, or at her best friend's house, drawing or talking about books.<br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Amber, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week! </div>
